First, we compute \(A^*A\):
\[A^*A = \begin{pmatrix} 2 & 0 \\ 3 & -2 \end{pmatrix} \begin{pmatrix}  2 & 3 \\ 0 & -2 \end{pmatrix} = \begin{pmatrix} 4 & 6 \\ 6 & 13 \end{pmatrix}.\]

Next, we find the eigenvalues of \(A^*A\). The eigenvalues \(\lambda\) satisfy the characteristic equation:
\[\det(A^*A - \lambda I) = \det\begin{pmatrix} 4 - \lambda & 6 \\ 6 & 13 - \lambda \end{pmatrix} = (4 - \lambda)(13 - \lambda) - 36 = \lambda^2 - 17\lambda + 28 = 0.\]

